  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON:  The proposed erection of two externally illuminated poster panels by reason of their excessive design, scale, prominent siting and illumination are considered to create visually dominant and harmful features when viewed from the surrounding streetscene along Hornsey Road and Caedmon Road. The development therefore fails to respect its local context and pattern of development while having a significant detrimental impact on the character and appearance of the surrounding area. The proposed retention of the advertisement panel is therefore considered to be contrary to polices D1 (Overall design), D4 (Designing in context), D11 (Alterations and extensions)  Env 11(Advertisements and signs) of Islington’s Unitary Development Plan 2002, Islington’s Urban design guidance 2006 and guidance contained within PPS 17."
